# Auth: Clerk & Data Access Security

All authentication is handled by Clerk. Users must **never** be able to read, modify, or delete data that belongs to another user.

## Getting the Current User

In Server Components and Server Actions, always get the user from Clerk. If no user is authenticated, redirect to the homepage — this is where the sign-in and sign-up modals are. Never redirect to `/sign-in`.

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) redirect("/");
```

## Always Scope Queries to the Current User

`decks` has a `clerkUserId` column. Every query on `decks` must filter by the authenticated user's `userId`.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — scoped to the current user
const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ❌ BAD — returns all decks for all users
const allDecks = await db.select().from(decks);
```

## Accessing Cards via Deck Ownership

`cards` belong to a `deck`, not directly to a user. Before reading, updating, or deleting cards, verify the parent deck belongs to the current user.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — verify deck ownership before touching cards
const deck = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)),
});
if (!deck) throw new Error("Not found");

// Now safe to query cards for this deck
```

## Mutations (Create / Update / Delete)

Always scope mutations with `clerkUserId` to prevent unauthorised writes:

```ts
// ✅ Update — must match both id AND clerkUserId
await db.update(decks)
  .set({ title })
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));

// ✅ Delete
await db.delete(decks)
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
```

## Server Action Pattern

In Server Actions, redirect unauthenticated users to the homepage:

```ts
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

export async function deleteDeck(deckId: string) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/");

  await db.delete(decks).where(
    and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId))
  );
}
```

Never trust IDs coming from the client alone — always pair them with the authenticated `userId`.
